reviews.text: I went there with my friends on holiday, it was really warm inside like 25+ degree, they’d turned on the air con but there was no doors lol I asked the staff to turn on the fan for us and she does it but I saw the temperature was like 23 degrees... and half hour later it turned to 25 degree, I hope they understand that we were having a hot pot in summer I supposed the restaurant is nice and cool, we ended up split the bill and we paid $350 on each. Overall, We can have a better meal at other place for $150-$200, it was actually not really yummy, thats why they only got 3/5 stars here....
Tasty spicy chill fish pot, I visit after 11pm, got discount and it is a nice place to enjoy with friends. Around HKD$200 - $300 per head

Consistently good clean hotpot... 
Can recommend the 'Kim yu' / char grilled fish pot...tasty...
My all-time favorite restaurant with group of friends. Price are relatively cheap and food is delicious.
